content.detailedDescription: My mother-in-law and i were standing outside my house facing west when we both noticed a bright reddish - orange light rising above well beyond the horizon. it went straight up. at first we thought it was plane, but the light was far too large and wasn't a strobe. it continued straight up until it disappeared. within about 15 seconds, we witnessed a second like of the same size and color rise up over the house ( again from well beyond the horizon in distance). it also came up from the same direction, due west, but instead of going straight up, it slowly tracked to the south. climbing in altitude the whole time until it disappeared too. i would estimate this all took place within about two minutes. i checked my watch for the time, 8:43 pm (pst). and then went into the house to grab my phone and check the directions using my compass app. i called the nws station in medford and reported it. they said their radar didn't track flight traffic. i tried calling the medford int'l airport, but couldn't get through to anyone. i then reported the sighting to kdrv tv. for the life of me it looked like a missile or rocket launch, but there are absolutely no military installations between here and the coast of oregon.
content.summary: Witnessed two rocket/missile-like objects/lights

content.detailedDescription:
Hello

i'm not sure what i saw or didn't see. i did not see a ufo or any e.T's so this will not be a very exciting story, but it is something that i can not explain. there is no explanation for what i saw. 

my event took place in northern ireland and this story takes us back to either 2010, 2011 or possibly 2012. the truth is i can't remember, i think it was in 2011. i can't remember the time of year at all, if i had to guess i'd say april or may. 

one night between 1am and 3am i was awoken from my sleep by our dog barking at something outside. i live in the country not really near anything. 
at first i assumed it was the dog barking at a fox or someting but as i lay there i noticed there was a much more vicious tone in her bark, so i assumed maybe there was an intruder or something. 
my bedroom is on the second floor so i have a good view of our back yard and the fields at the back of the house. there is also a lot of trees around our property. 
so i went to the window looked out through my blinds and could see the dog looking in a north/ northeast direction. my parents room extends out from the back of the house and was blocking my view plus it was a bit dark to see anything clearly beyond the tree line. it was a particularly bright night as i could see the dog in the yard at 2 or 3 in the morning. she is white so easy to make out. 
anyway she continued and continued to bark for maybe 20 minutes. now the strange thing was that she was barking like she was about to attack something or someone (which was very very unlike this dog as she is very timid and friendly and would never really bark) but she was barking for this amount of time and my parents did not wake up and she was right below their room and my mum would be a very light sleeper. 
she sort of stopped for a bit and i got back into bed. it was unlike me, i felt very uneasy for some reason. i knew something wasn't right so i couldn't sleep and then next thing maybe after 5 or 10 minutes the dog started going berserk again, and as i went to the window i couldn't see her any longer. 
i lifted the blinds completely up to improve my view. the next thing that happened is dorm thing i will never forget. 
there was a huge huge bright explosion of light that lite up the entirety of outside and strangely for a light who's source was outside, it lite up the inside of my room completely. 
the way i describe it to people is if someone took a photo of you on a disposable camera or something and held the the flash bit up at your eyes and took the photo you be blinded by the flash. it was like that expect strangely i wasn't blinded by it. 
it was a blue light, not yellow or white or a mix of colours, it was a really really bright blue powerful light. 
unfortunately the ending of this story doesn't end with me saying and then i saw a ufo. 
i have never been as afraid in my life, it was fear like i never felt. i turned, and ran straight for my bed. 
i don't remember getting into bed, or laying in bed thinking about what had just happened, or whether or not the dog continued to bark. i remember nothing after turning to run for my bed. 
strangely i woke up the next morning not having remembered anything about the event. 
it was only maybe a week or possibly more i remembered and told my parents. 
i know there's nothing special about seeing a light, it could have been a guy doing some fox hunting in one of the fields behind our house with one of those powerful lamps, or maybe it was a bolt of lightening. well it was an extremely calm night and there was no weird weather and i can tell you it was no lamp. this light was so strong and lite absolutely everything up. 
the  fact i can't remember even getting into bed creeps me out. 

anyway i hope you enjoyed reading about my experience. 
thanks
content.summary: Extreme light, dog goes crazy, and memory loss, only affected one family member

content.detailedDescription: I was smoking a cigarette at the rear patio of my girlfriends apartment at 7:20pm local time, when a brilliant white rapidly blinking light crossed the sky from south west to north east direction, with a directional change resembling a snake's slither. the blinking light travelled very quickly, too fast for a satellite pass, then it stopped abruptly, and hovered for some time maybe a minute or so. the lights, lights multiple (as the brilliance of the strobe seemed to emanate from alternating point, very close to each-other) changed to bright red as the object then descended, straight vertically, paused, descended further, like a falling leaf, paused, at which time i had to stand on a chair to view over neighbours roof, the object/light then shot off at high speed at that altitude (tree-top) toward the north east, out of view. my girlfriend was in the shower when i first viewed the object, and i, very excitedly, asked her to wrap a towel around herself, and come out to see this thing. she did this, and also witnessed the object from the time it was descending for the first time. the sky was partly cloudy, but the object was in clear sky at first, and hovered long enough for the clouds to draw closer to it. the cloud-base was around 2000 to 3000 feet, and only when the cloud was in the same space did i realise that the object was smaller, and closer, than i had at first guessed, because it was just below the clouds before descending. it occurred to me that this might be a drone, but was travelling very fast, over a long distance, in controlled airspace, and a drone is not a usual thing to see in this area, day or night.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
